title: For Sale:  Bulgarian Makarov Pistol, 9X18
postcontent:
Selling my Bulgarian Makarov pistol, 9x18 Makarov, with ammo and accessories.  The bright blue finish is flawless, and the gun appears to have been fired very little.  Date of manufacture is 1987.
This semi-automatic pistol was designed in the 1950s by Russian Nikolai Makarov.  His objective was to design a simple and reliable medium-powered pistol to be used as the sidearm of the Soviet Forces.  It was accepted by Russia in 1951 and has been a standard firearm ever since.  Recent developments may soon change that, but its place in history is secure.
The all-steel Makarov is both single and double action, with a decocking safety.  The overall simplicity of the gun is part of the genius of design, and allows the gun to be disassembled with very few tools.
Included with the gun is a correct military holster, with extra clip pouch and cleaning rod.  I'm also including nine boxes of 9x18 ammo, suitable for both practice and defense.  The gun will be in a padded plastic storage or carrying  case, and you get my collection of Makarov literature.
The durable, reliable Makarov is a lot of gun for the $450 price, especially when the cost of ammo is factored in.  It's small enough for concealed carry, and perfect for home or car defense.  Reply to my ad with your phone number and we'll meet so you can exame this Makarov pistol.  I know you won't be disappointed.  Please be prepared to show me your Oklahoma Driver's License for proof of residency.

In the post-War years, as 1911s became increasingly common in the civilian market, shooters and custom shops found new ways to upgrade their .45s. If you’re ready for a 1911 that brings you upgraded features without a custom shop price tag, look into the Loaded Series.
